result.name: Itamae Sushi

reviews.text: Nice and tasty. They've run out of tuna.... Again
Spacious but some order were missed

A chain japanese restaurant in Hong Kong.
Limited choice of japanese food at airport.
It should be the only restaurant offer sushi and sashimi.
Dont expect too much and it is a little bit expensive.
Set lunch or set dinner is provided, seems to be valuable in the menu.
This time i tried the assorted diced sashimi with rice.

We had lunch at this Sushi Restaurant at Hong Kong Airport.
We first looked for the running Sushi, but there was absolutely no Sushi on the conveyor belt.
So we ordered two combo meals. I asked if I could have salmon Nigiri instead of shrimp, because I don't like shrimps. The waitress agreed.
When the sushi came there were two shrimp Nigiri on my plate, so I asked if they could exchange them with salmon, like I ordered it. The waitress sent the head of service to me. She refused to comply with my request and explained to me that there were no changes possible to the combo menus.
When I pointed out that the waitress agreed with my order and that they should have told me at the time I asked for it, she responded that the waitress simply doesn't speak English good enough. When I told her that that was no excuse at an airport restaurant in a major international city, she just went away.
My wife had to wait for her small Sashimi plate so long that I was already finished with my meal when they finally brought it to the table.
The quality of the food itself was at best mediocre. The scallops on the Sashimi plate were not fresh.
The only good thing we can say about this restaurant is that it is not expensive, regarding the fact it's inside the airport.
